                                     ERS-2

   08/31/2000 -- IMPORTANT information for users of ERS-1 and ERS-2
   altimetry data from this site regarding:
     * The USO and SPTR corrections.
     * A 40.9 cm bias that exists bewteen the ERS-1 and ERS-2 altimeter
       ranges.

Description

   ESA's ERS-2 radar altimeter satellite was launched in April of 1995 in
   an orbit that extended coverage over the ice sheets to +/- 81.5 degrees
   and is still in operation. As of February 1998 we have received data
   from May 1995 to June 1997. This data has been processed and is online
   .

